<div id="review_3415025009" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3415025009" />
    <a title="Ruth Hawes" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/29393232-ruth-hawes"><img alt="Ruth Hawes" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1599685414p2/29393232.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3415025009?book_show_action=true">Aug 21, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ruth Hawes" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ruth Hawes" href="/user/show/29393232-ruth-hawes">Ruth Hawes</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781771803663" href="/book/show/49005459-we-of-the-forsaken-world">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3415025009" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13037807358220254008">Wow. Kiran Bhat has created a true masterpiece that blends time, genres and communities across the globe in this beautiful modern tale of life itself. Like communication networks stories connect in so many different ways that we never thought possible. This book tells life from the perspective of different people with each account being unique in it&apos;s own way. But the way these stories come together and almagamate into one is trulty a work of literary genius. <br/><br/>Kiran Bhat brings to life difficult </span>
  <span id="freeText13037807358220254008" style="display:none">Wow. Kiran Bhat has created a true masterpiece that blends time, genres and communities across the globe in this beautiful modern tale of life itself. Like communication networks stories connect in so many different ways that we never thought possible. This book tells life from the perspective of different people with each account being unique in it's own way. But the way these stories come together and almagamate into one is trulty a work of literary genius. <br /><br />Kiran Bhat brings to life difficult topics like abuse, rape and trafficking in a way that it does not seem horrible but brings the real truth of it to life. This is very difficult to do as most novels cover over the truth not wanting to discuss these topics in such a way. However, this book is different and it really shows the negative effects these can have on people. I also loved the style of writing and I could not put this book down. Would recommend this to anyone who wants to read a book that is honest and beautiful but expresses the true meaning of life in a way I never thought possible. </span>
  <a data-text-id="13037807358220254008" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review3415025009">
